Transportation Secretary ElizabethDole proposed to allow the use of daytime running lights as ameasure to improve safety on the highways.    Dole said in an announcement that in Sweden and Finland, where daytime lights have been in use, the number of crashesand lives lost has been reduced.    The transporation department said there might be confusionin some states whether the lighting device was legal.    Therefore it proposed an amendment to federal motor vehiclesafety rules to make clear that front-mounted lights could beinstalled at the option of the manufacturer. Reuter&#3;